Given I'm logged-in with valid credentials
When I select 'Male' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'MRI pelvic floor' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
Then I go to Page 08 of Pelvic MRI
And I click on 'Finding' radio button
And dropdown below 'Finding' is enabled

When I select 'Sigma mass' from the dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Characterization I' tab is preselected

When I select 'Differential diagnosis' tab
Then 'Differential diagnosis 1*' dropdown is enabled

When I select 'Sigmoid colon cancer' from 'Differential diagnosis 1*' dropdown
Then 'T1: Infiltration submucosa' radio button is enabled
And 'T2: Infiltration muscularis propria' radio button is enabled
And 'T3: Infiltration of muscularis propria/subserosa or in non-peritonealised pericolic tissue' radio button is enabled
And 'T4: Infiltration of visceral peritoneum or direct organ infiltration' radio button is enabled
And 'Suspicion of' checkbox is enabled
And 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown is enabled

When I select 'T4: Infiltration of visceral peritoneum or direct organ infiltration' radio button
Then 'T4a: Peritoneum' radio button is enabled
And 'T4b: Other adjacent organs' radio button is enabled

When I select 'T4b: Other adjacent organs' radio button
Then 'Urinary bladder' checkbox is enabled
And 'Prostate' checkbox is enabled
And 'Seminal vesicles' checkbox is enabled
And 'Peritoneum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Abdomen/pelvic wall' checkbox is enabled
And 'Small intestine' checkbox is enabled
And 'Left external iliac vessels' checkbox is enabled

When I select any other option from the 'Differential diagnosis 1*' dropdown
Then an option is selected

When I select 'Sigmoid colon cancer' from 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown
Then 'T1: Infiltration submucosa' radio button is enabled
And 'T2: Infiltration muscularis propria' radio button is enabled
And 'T3: Infiltration of muscularis propria/subserosa or in non-peritonealised pericolic tissue' radio button is enabled
And 'T4: Infiltration of visceral peritoneum or direct organ infiltration' radio button is enabled
And 'Subordinate' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'T4: Infiltration of visceral peritoneum or direct organ infiltration' radio button
Then 'T4a: Peritoneum' radio button is enabled
And 'T4b: Other adjacent organs' radio button is enabled

When I select 'T4b: Other adjacent organs' radio button
Then 'Urinary bladder' checkbox is enabled
And 'Prostate' checkbox is enabled
And 'Seminal vesicles' checkbox is enabled
And 'Peritoneum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Abdomen/pelvic wall' checkbox is enabled
And 'Small intestine' checkbox is enabled
And 'Left external iliac vessels' checkbox is enabled
